### 🐛 BUG 1 (Critical): `autoFillQueue()` Blocked for Playlist/Album Context — Causes Playback to End

**File:** [PlaybackViewModel.kt](file:///C:/Users/ajaye/AndroidStudioProjects/OfflineMediaPlayer/app/src/main/java/com/local/offlinemediaplayer/viewmodel/PlaybackViewModel.kt#L1472-L1523)

**The Problem:**
When you shuffle a playlist or album (via `playPlaylist()` or `playAlbum()`), the `_currentPlaylistContext` is set to a non-null value (e.g., the playlist ID or `"ALBUM_123"`). When all songs in that context finish playing and `STATE_ENDED` is reached, the `onPlaybackStateChanged` callback calls `autoFillQueue(playNext = true)`.

However, `autoFillQueue()` has this guard at [line 1481](file:///C:/Users/ajaye/AndroidStudioProjects/OfflineMediaPlayer/app/src/main/java/com/local/offlinemediaplayer/viewmodel/PlaybackViewModel.kt#L1481):

```kotlin
if (_currentPlaylistContext.value != null && !playPrevious) {
    return  // ← EXITS EARLY, playback STOPS
}
```

This is **intentionally designed** to prevent random library songs from being appended when playing a specific playlist/album. The intent is correct — if you queue a 10-song album, you don't want 500 random songs auto-appended.

**But the issue is:** When `REPEAT_MODE_OFF` is used (the default), playback simply **stops** after the last shuffled song. The user sees the player idle with no indication of why it stopped. This is the "music ends after some songs" problem you're experiencing.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is NOT a bug in the shuffle logic itself. Media3's shuffle correctly plays all songs. The problem is that with `REPEAT_MODE_OFF` + playlist context, there's nothing to play after the queue ends. The fix depends on the desired UX.

**Proposed Fix:** When shuffle is enabled and the queue reaches `STATE_ENDED`, automatically set `REPEAT_MODE_ALL` for the shuffle session (so it loops through the shuffled songs indefinitely), OR clear the playlist context when shuffle is toggled from the Now Playing screen so `autoFillQueue` can append more songs.

